SUMMARY:Your Voice on Stage: The Iterative Pitch Lab
DESCRIPTION:Are you an underrepresented voice in cloud native looking to share your expertise on stage but need guidance on how to begin? We’re here to help! Join seasoned KubeCon+CloudNativeCon speakers and past program committee members for a hands-on workshop focused on crafting standout talk proposals.\n\nThis isn't a passive lecture. You’ll work in short\, focused cycles learning a key pitching principle\, immediately applying it\, and receiving instant\, constructive feedback through guided peer critiques. We’ll cover choosing compelling topics\, writing a strong title and abstract\, and highlighting your unique perspective for the right audience. We’ll also show best practices for using AI as a companion to refine your story for your next session on stage.\n\nThe session culminates in a live Q&A where you’ll get real-time feedback on your proposals\, giving you a blueprint for success. Walk away with a refined talk abstract\, actionable insights\, expert guidance\, and the confidence to turn your expertise into a conference submission!
CATEGORIES:INCLUSION + ACCESSIBILITY
LOCATION:G104 - 105 | Community Hub\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
