BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260317T131510Z
DTSTART:20260326T112500Z
DTEND:20260326T115000Z
SUMMARY:Cloud Native Theater | KubeVirt Summit: Achieving 10× Faster VM Migration to KubeVirt with Storage Offload in Forklift - Ryosuke Tatsumi\, Hitachi America\, Ltd.
DESCRIPTION:Migrating large-scale production virtual machines (VMs) from VMware environments to KubeVirt remains a key adoption challenge for the community\, primarily due to slow data migration and limited scalability of host-based data copy approaches.\n\nIn this session\, we present an enhancement to Forklift\, an open-source toolkit for migrating VMs to KubeVirt\, that introduces a storage offload acceleration mechanism using XCOPY\, a standard storage I/O command. This work extends the open-source migration pipeline to offload bulk data movement from compute nodes to the storage layer.\n\nThis approach significantly reduces host CPU\, memory\, and network consumption and achieves up to 10× faster VM migrations compared to traditional methods. The design supports both cold and warm migration workflows and is engineered to scale to thousands of VMs\, addressing a common pain point reported by KubeVirt users operating at scale.\n\nWe will discuss how this contribution can be reused\, adapted\, or extended by the broader KubeVirt community to improve VM migration performance across diverse environments.
CATEGORIES:SOLUTIONS SHOWCASE
LOCATION:Hall 1-5 | Tram Zone | Cloud Native Theater\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:8c926efe61e49ac143bcef9315497c99
URL:http://kccnceu2026.sched.com/event/8c926efe61e49ac143bcef9315497c99
